Credit Suisse Appoints Kazmi Head of Middle East Mergers

-- B y   S t e f a n i a   B i a n c h i
-- 
2011-05-18T14:13:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/credit-suisse-names-kazmi-head-of-mideast-mergers-acquisitions.html
Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  appointed
Mumtaz Kazmi as head of mergers and acquisitions in the Middle
East and North Africa, replacing Erwin Van Der Voort, according
to a document obtained by Bloomberg News.  Der Voort has moved to  New York  where he will focus on
advising hedge funds, according to the document.  Separately, Nick Koemtzopoulos will oversee equity capital
markets in the Middle East and North Africa, replacing George Pavey who will move to Hong Kong, it said. Koemtzopoulos will
remain as head of emerging markets ECM for Europe, Middle East
and Africa.  A spokesperson for Credit Suisse confirmed the moves.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Stefania Bianchi in Dubai at 
